        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200802/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-02"><time>2020-08-02</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Tile-and-con­crete floors and long wooden ta­bles and benches cre­ate an in­for­mal set­ting that en­cour­ages con­vivi­al­ity among the largely hip­ster clien­tele.</p>
    <p>Be­ing away from town in a hid­den cor­ner of Kal­lang River­side Park gives it an in­sider appeal.</p>
    <p>But with the room made up of just hard sur­faces, be prepared to be deaf­ened when the place fills up with peo­ple and con­ver­sa­tion.</p>
    <p>The bot­tom line: Is it worth pay­ing $80 for the pizza here? If you have deep pock­ets, go ahead. But there are other good margherita piz­zas in town going for less than $30. Some even have one-for-one deals in this cli­mate.</p>

